Example files were generated by running (in the top level directory, not the
example directory):

perl -Ilib script/make_test_fasta.pl --seed 10 --seq_region_count 10 \
--seq_region_max_length 500 > example/example.fa
samtools faidx example/example.fa
perl -Ilib script/make_test_sam.pl --seed 10 --seq_region_count 10 \
--seq_region_max_length 500 --read_pair_count 50 \
--read_tags NNNNBGAGGC NNNNBAGAAG \
| samtools view -bS - | samtools sort - example/example1
samtools view -h example/example1.bam \
| perl -Ilib script/perturb_sam.pl --seed 10 \
| samtools view -bS - | samtools sort - example/example2
samtools view -h example/example1.bam \
| perl -Ilib script/perturb_sam.pl --seed 20 \
| samtools view -bS - | samtools sort - example/example3
ls example/example*.bam | xargs -n1 samtools index

To run the example differential expression pipeline (again from the top level
directory):

perl -Ilib script/run_de_pipeline.pl --scheduler local --dir tmp \
--analysis_yaml example/de-analysis.yaml --stages_yaml example/de.yaml \
--sleep_time 1 --verbose

Or (using LSF):

perl -Ilib script/run_de_pipeline.pl --dir tmp \
--analysis_yaml example/de-analysis.yaml --stages_yaml example/de.yaml \
--sleep_time 60 --verbose

To run the example downsampling pipeline (again from the top level directory):

wget https://github.com/iansealy/picard-detct/releases/download/v1.79-detct/picard-tools-1.79-detct.zip
unzip picard-tools-1.79-detct.zip

perl -Ilib script/run_downsample_pipeline.pl --scheduler local --dir tmp \
--analysis_yaml example/downsample-analysis.yaml \
--stages_yaml example/downsample.yaml \
--sleep_time 1 --verbose

Or (using LSF):

perl -Ilib script/run_downsample_pipeline.pl --dir tmp \
--analysis_yaml example/downsample-analysis.yaml \
--stages_yaml example/downsample.yaml \
--sleep_time 60 --verbose
